place.name: WADENHOE
place.gazetteerText: WADENHOE, a parish in Oundle district, Northampton; 4 miles SSW of Oundle r. station. It has a post-office under Oundle. Acres, 1,150. Real property, £1,623. Pop., 270. Houses, 56. The manor, with W. House, belongs to G. W. Hunt, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Peterborough. Value, £286.* Patron, G. Capron, Esq. The church is old. There is a national school. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
